gomodel:SYNGO_3048  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Synaptic distribution of Bcl11A in neurons revealed by immunofluorescence staining\"\n\nFig.5: \"Subcellular distribution of Bcl11A in rat brain revealed by biochemical fractionation\"\n- \"The relative intensity of these protein bands differed among the subcellular compartments, suggesting differential posttranslational modification of Bcl11A-L in different fractions. Immunoblotting of PSD-95 (Fig. 5B) was performed again to ensure the quality of these biochemical fractions (Hsueh and Sheng,1999a). The presence of Bcl11A-S and Bcl11A-L proteins in the crude synaptic membrane and crude synaptic vesicle fractions is consistent with the observation that Bcl11A immunoreactivity was colocalized with synaptophysin in cultured hippocampal neurons, confirming a synaptic distribution of BCl11A. To further elucidate this, the presence of Bcl11A proteins in the postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions was examined. The result showed that Bcl11A-L was enriched in the PSD I and PSD II fractions (Fig. 5C). In contrast, the PSD I and PSD II fractions had only a trace amount of Bcl11A-S (Fig. 5C). This analysis suggested that Bcl11A-L is the major form of postsynaptic Bcl11A protein.\"\n\n28/3/2018 Pim\n- The authors claim enrichment in the PSD fraction that I cannot really confirm. I have annotated to the less specific term 'postsynapse'.. Experimental description: - Title: \"Expression of zinc finger transcription factor Bcl11A/Evi9/CTIP1 in rat brain\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3048" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

